three daughters and is a widower. He brings the family to his parent&amp;#039;s 

house for a family get-together. When Dan goes to a local bookstore, he 

meets a woman, Marie (Juliette Binoche). To catch her attention, Dan 

poses as a shop clerk, and convinces her to buy a random selection of 

books. When Marie finds out the truth, Dan proposes to make it up to 

her. The two share an intimate conversation and Dan starts falling for 

her. Marie, gets a phone call and starts to leave immediately. Dan asks 

for her number. Marie refuses saying that she has just started a new 

relationship, but relents and gives Dan her number.

